[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating build processes**\n\nRunning Gradle might create build directories, which I’d like to avoid if possible. Maybe using the Maven dependency tree is a better approach since it reads from and writes to .m2 but doesn't modify the repository. I need to parse POM parents for versions and consider what setup is necessary before achieving meaningful test coverage for the Forge workflow. I'll check the Doxia site renderer for dependencies and ensure we have the correct parsers for APT input.\n\n**Reviewing rendering coverage**\n\nTo achieve meaningful coverage of the public API rendering, using just the xhtml5 parser might be enough. I need to find out if the default scaffold includes only the tested library without optional test dependencies. The generated agent can add code but not build dependencies unless we have a deterministic setup. I wonder if we need an additional dependency for the usual formats. I’ll inspect the source and tests for version 2.0.0 to check normal test dependencies. A source jar could also be useful.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09484f402eda1f2a016a3f6c090a1c81908620f89b7b264786\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP2wSeUd3JBouv5R-Zk6lOSf1nVWEKQPgUfEF2O_D-lmRVomgRzoeNsN599zdfzFKD-fhW---Ly9rteT3D2czaAsO56OzNayw6P0BLvKzLXNvyWzhEcejoGsx4IOXhuN7sHqYTlJjI70MSFrkOxnq9ZGaFdWtLvYd1cCqpvFcipgVMwmnYds39mAzomNjrtAB56mbOEIQBJ3HozJqm91NKDPAaajPOfz2Jc1FhB-uUv1G4rJffllPxqVHcH0j3JojA-gkk2rg-gf3qQlD5WCEGkF6AXAdu8gv09sxEyR-3OVKUsoeuFUSn1ATalBTUSm21eF3qPJ5RuBmJNAMnq5Iv8VjHn3WdB2clmaZUxZfjrBKF7sgCAVnvOVhxuuuhfI2NTg7p2dYPsizlobskhJ2UZ5rrYaYhVbXUee3iCeys8gxwqEjBaBIV_0Gl5sxqRG-EnVajXlVvVMD1qSwhrCe3n93y-Ai-meI6mYAzXpE_j9LZzGLASr82apyQ-u2wt8c6-aiiJ0zyYbVZ9F1KRQNcykR9B6ZUBOODe9-VdUaQ_o4Bok1ba2ucTJTGS-n1Hh8GGQTAZlZwrwonduzT39_mnpAQu6e4DVshJkn1RQzbk35rxdfttzOE6DEx5LE6tPiI4NYdp21-ZcpF-sZ2FCkNfyWkqrG6r1xsFxs7DPolKzmUQ7Q