 SiteRenderer.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The 2.0.0 public skin APIs expose org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact, but doxia-site-renderer declares maven-artifact as provided, so the generated test scaffold will not receive it transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"APT parser components are not part of doxia-core in 2.0.0; the upstream POM adds this module so ParserModuleManager can discover the component descriptor for normal site documents.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-xdoc:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"XDoc parser components are not part of doxia-core in 2.0.0; the upstream POM adds this module so ParserModuleManager can discover the component descriptor for normal site documents.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-fml:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"FML parser components are not part of doxia-core in 2.0.0; the upstream POM adds this module so ParserModuleManager can discover the component descriptor for FAQ-style site documents.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use the 2.0.0 API rather than the removed 1.x types and methods: RenderingContext and SkinResourceLoader are gone, DefaultSiteRenderer no longer has enableLogging, and SiteRenderingContext no longer has setUsingDefaultTemplate. Initialize SiteRenderingContext with a SiteModel, Locale, templateName, and templateClassLoader; for skin/resource coverage, create a temporary skin JAR containing META-INF/maven/site.vm and any non-META-INF resources to copy.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated tests only exercise the transitive xhtml5 parser and protected velocity-context helpers, the extra parser modules may be more than strictly necessary.\",\n    \"Plexus/Sisu/Guice-based initialization is closer to normal use but can add native-image surface area; local Gradle and native-image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09484f402eda1f2a016a3f6cb031b081908f668e34fec221ea\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1143, "output": 1193, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 60704, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782541479041, "responseId": "resp_09484f402eda1f2a016a3f6ca7a4b88190855942d30937db8e"}}
